children.name: Rules
children.text:
This copper ring is hammered flat and twisted to look like a curled palm leaf.
While attuned to this ring, you can use an action to expend one or more of its five charges to cast Elemental Weapon. Expending one charge casts the spell at 3rd level, expending three of the charges casts the spell at 5th level. The ring regains 1d4 expended charges daily at dawn. If you expend the ring's last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the ring crumbles into ashes and is destroyed.
